cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about medical image segmentation using an adversarial neural network. The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks and multi-scale loss functions, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a min-max game, which is a common technique in adversarial networks and reinforcement learning (cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses datasets from the MICCAI BRATS brain tumor segmentation challenge, which is related to medical imaging (cs.MM).
